369  GPS_STATUS_FIX_3D = (int)0x00000300,
370  GPS_STATUS_FIX_GPS_PLUS_DEAD_RECK = (int)0x00000400,
371  GPS_STATUS_FIX_TIME_ONLY = (int)0x00000500,
372  GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED1 = (int)0x00000600,
373  GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED2 = (int)0x00000700,
374  GPS_STATUS_FIX_DGPS = (int)0x00000800,
375  GPS_STATUS_FIX_SBAS = (int)0x00000900,
376  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_SINGLE = (int)0x00000A00,
377  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FLOAT = (int)0x00000B00,
378  GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX = (int)0x00000C00,
379  GPS_STATUS_FIX_MASK = (int)0x00001F00,
380  GPS_STATUS_FIX_BIT_OFFSET = (int)8,
381 
383  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_FIX_OK = (int)0x00010000, // within limits (e.g. DOP & accuracy)
384  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_DGPS_USED = (int)0x00020000, // Differential GPS (DGPS) used.
385  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_FIX_AND_HOLD = (int)0x00040000, // RTK feedback on the integer solutions to drive the float biases towards the resolved integers
386 // GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_WEEK_VALID = (int)0x00040000,
387 // GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_TOW_VALID = (int)0x00080000,
388  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_ENABLED = (int)0x00100000, // RTK precision positioning mode enabled
389  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_STATIC_MODE = (int)0x00200000, // Static mode
390  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED = (int)0x00400000, // RTK moving base mode enabled
391  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR = (int)0x00800000, // RTK error: observations or ephemeris are invalid or not received (i.e. RTK differential corrections)
392  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_DATA_MISSING = (int)0x01000000, // RTK error: Either base observations or antenna position have not been received.
393  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MOVING = (int)0x02000000, // RTK error: base position moved when it should be stationary
394  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_INVALID = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position is invalid or not surveyed well
395  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position error bitmask
396  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_ERROR_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR|
397  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK),
398  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID = (int)0x04000000, // RTK precision position is valid on GPS1 (i.e. < 20cm accuracy)
399  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID = (int)0x08000000, // RTK moving base heading is valid on GPS2
400  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD = (int)0x00002000,
401  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET = (int)0x00004000,
402  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED|
403  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID|
404  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD|
405  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET),
406  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_GPS_NMEA_DATA = (int)0x00008000, // 1 = Data from NMEA message
407  GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_MASK = (int)0x0FFFE000,

3727 #define LE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
3728 #define LE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
3729 #define LE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
3730 #else // little endian
3731 #define BE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
3732 #define BE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
3733 #define BE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
3734 #define BE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
3735 #define LE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
3736 #define LE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
3737 #define LE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
3738 #define LE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
